        "id": 280020,
        "name": "James Welz",
        "username": "hoofman",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/h/8edcca/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-11-24T18:27:46.744Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Please add a hidden emergency button (or secret code like !!911) that does this in one tap:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Reads my GPS once</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Looks up the correct emergency Signal number / group for my country or city from a tiny list that comes with the app (same size as the spam list you already ship)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Instantly sends a pre-written message: “DURESS – I am in danger – DO NOT reply or call – this phone may be taken from me – location attached” + live location + optional 10-second ambient audio</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The message disappears from MY phone the second it is sent — even if someone forces me to open Signal afterwards, they see nothing.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>This would save lives for domestic-violence victims, activists, journalists, and everyday people in dangerous situations — without any government cooperation. Everything needed already exists inside Signal today (location sharing, disappearing messages, encrypted audio notes, offline blocklist updates). All that’s missing is one new button and a tiny open database of verified emergency contacts per country (volunteers and NGOs can keep it updated on GitHub).</p>\n<p>This is not science fiction — lone-worker panic apps already do almost exactly this. Please make Signal the first mainstream messenger that truly protects people under coercion.</p>\n<p>Thank you.</p>",
