        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/ccd318/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-11-25T00:02:36.605Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Generally, this is a nice idea, but there are some issues with it, I think.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"hoofman\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"73124\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/h/8edcca/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> hoofman:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Reads my GPS once</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Signal can not turn on GPS if it isn’t already enabled and even if it is, this requires constant access. (not that I don’t trust Signal, but fewer permissions are always better in my opinion)</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"hoofman\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"73124\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/h/8edcca/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> hoofman:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>emergency Signal number / group</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I’m not sure if this exists in a lot of places. I don’t think it does.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"hoofman\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"73124\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/h/8edcca/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> hoofman:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>live location</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Signal doesn’t currently support live location sharing, so this message could at most contain one single location at a fixed time.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"hoofman\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"73124\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/h/8edcca/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> hoofman:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>without any government cooperation</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>If it isn’t a government contact, who would be providing the emergency number? How would Signal ensure that the number is trustworthy and reliable?</p>",
